# Docker validation

Full guides: `docs/deployment/docker.md`, `docs/deployment/production.md`

## When required

Run `pnpm run docker:validate` before opening a PR when changes touch:

- `docker/` (compose, Dockerfiles, init scripts)
- `packages/database/` (migrations, schema)
- API or worker database/Redis/queue integrations
- Any new feature depending on Postgres, Redis, or MinIO

## Commands

```bash
make docker-up        # start local infra
pnpm run docker:validate  # full health check + teardown
make check            # includes docker:validate
```

## Image standards

- Pin image versions — never `latest` in committed compose files
- Alpine/slim base images where possible
- Non-root user in production Dockerfiles
- Health checks on every service
- Memory limits defined
- Dev ports bound to `127.0.0.1` only

Pre-commit runs `validate` (fast). `docker:validate` runs in `make check` and CI.
